Meet <b>Natalia</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>This raven-haired resident lives at <a href='/home/?user=huneebee'>63284 Clover Lane</a> in Lakeview, and you'll often find her hanging out by the water seemingly lost in her own thoughts. Since July 19, 2006, Natalia has impressed everyone in Millsberry with her quirky comments, love of languages, and her striking wardrobe.  <br><br>Though her favorite colors are black, red, and dark blue, she's hardly the gloomy type. Creativity is her strength, and she never shies away from trying something new. She's got a real knack with words, and loves doing crossword puzzles in her free time. Her expertise with language extends into the realm of computer languages as well! She's rarely seen without her PortaByte laptop, with which she plays games, keeps in touch with faraway friends, and makes digital artwork. <br><br>But aside from creativity, she excels at thinking logically. Her ability to think through problems has helped make her a <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=380">Sudoku</a> and <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=12">Solver</a> champ. In fact, she has quite a collection of trophies! She says that instead of competing with other citizens, she is instead challenging herself to be her personal best. Her determination is really admirable, and her friends look up to her. <br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Natalia, and congratulations on being named citizen of the week! </div>
